description:
In rust/lichen-rpl/src/routing.rs:67, when address bytes don't divide evenly by 16:

    if !addr_bytes.len().is_multiple_of(16) {
        return Err(TooShort::new(data.len() + (16 - addr_bytes.len() % 16), data.len()).into());
    }

This error message is misleading. TooShort is meant for 'buffer too short' errors, but here the buffer has extra trailing bytes that don't form a complete address. The error type is correct but the 'expected' value calculation is confusing - it suggests padding to the next 16-byte boundary, which isn't the actual requirement.

Location: rust/lichen-rpl/src/routing.rs:67
Risk: Confusing error messages during debugging.
Fix: Use a different error variant (e.g., InvalidLength) or clarify the error message.
